                <h4>Statistics</h4>

    
              <p>One of:</p>
    
              <ul class="program-set">
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/aema-310" class="program-course-title">
              AEMA 310 Statistical Methods 1 (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-17358" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Plant Science (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/606">Agricultural &amp; Environmental Sciences</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Mathematics (Agric&amp;Envir Sci)              : Measures of central tendency and dispersion; binomial and Poisson distributions; normal, chi-square, Student's t and Fisher-Snedecor F distributions; estimation and hypothesis testing; simple linear regression and correlation; analysis of variance for simple experimental designs.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014, Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Pierre R L Dutilleul, Valérie Gravel (Fall)                  Pierre R L Dutilleul, Valérie Gravel (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Two 1.5-hour lectures and one 2-hour lab</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
